egiment]] || Lieut. Col. Simon P. Ohr\n|-\n| [[106th Illinois Infantry Regiment]] || Lieut. Col. Henry Yates\n|-\n| [[12th Michigan Volunteer Infantry Regiment]] || Lieut. Col. [[Dwight May]]\n|-\n| rowspan=5 | Second Brigade<br>Col. [[Oliver Wood (general)|Oliver Wood]]\n| [[126th Illinois Infantry Regiment]] || Lieut. Col. Ezra M. Beardsley\n|-\n| [[40th Iowa Volunteer Infantry Regiment]] || Lieut. Col. Samuel F. Cooper\n|-\n| [[3rd Minnesota Volunteer Infantry Regiment]] || Col. [[Christopher Columbus Andrews|Christopher C. Andrews]]\n|-\n| [[22nd Ohio Infantry|22nd Ohio Infantry Regiment]] || Lieut. Col. Homer Thrall\n|-\n| [[27th Wisconsin Volunteer Infantry Regiment]] || Col. [[Conrad Krez]]\n|-\n| rowspan=6 | '''Third Division'''<br>Brig. Gen. [[Samuel Allen Rice]]<br>[[File:Samuelallenricecommons.jpg|thumb|center|upright=0.3|Rice]]\n| rowspan=3 | First Brigade<br>Col. Charles W. Kittredge\n| [[43rd Indiana Infantry Regiment]] || Lieut. Col. John C. Major\n|-\n| [[36th Iowa Volunteer Infantry Regiment]] || Lieut. Col. Francis M. Drake\n|-\n| [[77th Ohio Infantry|77th Ohio Infantry Regiment]] || Col. William B. Mason\n|-\n| rowspan=3 | Second Brigade<br>Col. Thomas H. Benton Jr. \n| [[29th Iowa Volunteer Infantry Regiment]] || Lieut. Col. Robert F. Patterson\n|-\n| [[33rd Iowa Volunteer Infantry Regiment]] || Lieut. Col. Cyrus H. Mackey\n|-\n| [[28th Wisconsin Volunteer Infantry Regiment]] || Maj. Calvert C. White\n|- \n| rowspan=2 | '''Independent Cavalry'''\n| rowspan=2 | Independent Brigade<br>Col. [[Powell Clayton]]\n| [[1st Indiana Cavalry Regiment]] || Lieut. Col. Thomas N. Pace\n|-\n| [[5th Kansas Volunteer Cavalry Regiment]] || Lieut. Col. Wilton A. Jenkins\n|-\n| rowspan=5 | '''Independent Infantry'''\n| rowspan=5 | Independent Brigade<br>Col. James M. True\n| [[49th Illinois Infantry Regiment]] || Col. Phineas Pease\n|-\n| [[62nd Illinois Infantry Regiment]] || Lieut. Col. Stephen M. Meeker\n|-\n| [[50th Indiana Infantry Regiment]] || Lieut. Col. Samuel T. Wells\n|-\n| [[27th Iowa Volunteer Infantry Regiment]] || Col. [[James Isham Gilbert]]\n|-\n| [[Springfield Illinois Light Artillery]] (6 3.8-in JR){{sfn|Swain|2015}} || Capt. Thomas F. Vaughn\n|-\n| rowspan=4 | '''Independent Artillery'''\n| rowspan=4 | Artillery Brigade<br>Capt. Mortimer M. Haden\n| [[3rd Iowa Independent Battery Light Artillery]]<br>(4 6lb Gun, 3 12lb How, 1 3-in OR, 1 10lb PR){{sfn|Swain|2018a}} || 1st Lieut. Melvil C. Wright\n|-\n| [[Battery K, 1st Missouri Light Artillery]] (4 10lb PR){{sfn|Swain|2019a}} || Capt. Stillman O. Fish\n|-\n| [[5th Ohio Battery]] (2 6lb Gun, 2 3.8-in JR){{sfn|Swain|2018b}} || 1st Lieut. John D. Burner\n|-\n| [[11th Ohio Battery]] (2 6lb Gun, 2 12lb How, 1 6lb Rifle){{sfn|Swain|2018b}} || Capt. Frank C. Sands\n|-\n|}\n\n==Confederate forces==\nConfederate Army: Maj. Gen. [[Sterling Price]]\n*On July 23, 1863, the department commander Lieut. Gen. [[Theophilus H. Holmes]] became ill and was superseded by Price.{{sfn|Dimitry|Harrell|1899|p=208}}  \n*On September 6, 1863, Brig. Gen. Marmaduke mortally wounded Brig. Gen. Walker in a duel. Col. Dobbins assumed command of Walker's division.{{sfn|Dimitry|Harrell|1899|pp=220\u2013221}} \n*Marmaduke placed Dobbins under arrest on September 10 for disobedience of orders and command devolved upon Col. Newton. Price later suspended Dobbins's arrest.{{sfn|Dimitry|Harrell|1899|pp=221\u2013222}}\n*Present for duty: 7,749. About 6,500 were north of the Arkansas River and 1,250 south of the river.{{sfn|Battles & Leaders|1987|p=457}}\n*Aggregate present (September): 10,665, 32 guns. Present for duty: 8,532.{{sfn|Dimitry|Harrell|1899|p=207}}\n*Casualties: 12 killed, 34 wounded, 18 missing.{{sfn|Battles & Leaders|1987|p=461}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; width:75%;\"\n|+Confederate Army: Little Rock Expedition{{sfn|Official Records|1888}}{{sfn|Battles & Leaders|1987|p=461}}\n! width=15% | Division\n! width=15% | Brigade\n! width=30% | Unit\n! width=15% | Commander\n|-\n| rowspan=9 | '''Marmaduke's Cavalry Division'''<br>Brig. Gen. [[John S. Marmaduke]]<br>[[File:General John S. Marmaduke, C.S.A. (9241066570).jpg|thumb|center|upright=0.3|Marmaduke]]\n| rowspan=4 | [[Shelby's Iron Brigade|Shelby's Brigade]]<br>Lieut. Col. [[Benjamin Franklin Gordon|Benjamin F. Gordon]]\n| [[5th Missouri Cavalry Regiment (Confederate)|5th Missouri Cavalry Regiment]] || Lieut. Col. B. F. Gordon\n|-\n| [[6th Missouri Cavalry Regiment (Confederate)|6th Missouri Cavalry Regiment]] || Col. [[Gideon W. Thompson]]\n|-\n| [[10th Missouri Cavalry Battalion (Confederate)|10th Missouri Cavalry Battalion]] || Maj. Benjamin Elliott\n|-\n| [[2nd Missouri Field Battery (Confederate)|2nd Missouri Field Battery]] (2 6lb Gun, 2 10lb PR){{sfn|McGhee|2008|p=7}} || Capt. Joseph Bledsoe\n|-\n| rowspan=5 | Marmaduke's Brigade<br>Col. William L. Jeffers\n| [[8th Missouri Cavalry Regiment (Confederate)|8th Missouri Cavalry Regiment]] || Lieut. Col. S. J. Ward\n|-\n| [[3rd Missouri Cavalry Regiment (Confederate)|3rd Missouri Cavalry Regiment]] || Maj. L. A. Campbell\n|-\n| [[4th Missouri Cavalry Regiment (Confederate)|4th Missouri Cavalry Regiment]] || Lieut. Col. W. J. Preston\n|-\n| [[11th Missouri Cavalry Battalion (Confederate)|11th Missouri Cavalry Battalion]] || Lieut. Col. M. L. Young\n|-\n| Prairie Gun Battery, Missouri Artillery || 1st Lieut. T. J. Williams\n|-\n| rowspan=8 | '''Walker's Cavalry Division'''<br>Brig. Gen. [[Lucius M. Walker]]<br>Col. [[Archibald S. Dobbins]]<br>Col. [[Robert C. Newton]]<br>[[File:LMWalker.jpg|thumb|center|upright=0.3|Walker]]\n| rowspan=3 | Dobbin's Brigade<br>Col. A. S. Dobbins<br>Col. R. C. Newton\n| [[1st Arkansas Cavalry Regiment (Dobbin's)]] || Maj. S. Corley ('''k''')<br>Capt. M. M. Bateman\n|-\n| [[5th Arkansas Cavalry Regiment]] || Col. R. C. Newton, Maj. J. P. Bull\n|-\n| [[6th Arkansas Field Battery]] || Capt. C. B. Etter\n|-\n| rowspan=5 | Carter's Brigade<br>Col. George W. Carter\n| [[21st Texas Cavalry Regiment]]{{sfn|Bailey|2011}}<ref group=note>The 21st Texas Cavalry was picketing the Arkansas River and missed the fighting.</ref> || Lieut. Col. [[Dewitt Clinton Giddings|Dewitt C. Giddings]]\n|-\n| [[Morgan's Texas Cavalry Battalion|Morgan's Texas Cavalry Squadron]] || Maj. Charles L. Morgan\n|-\n| Johnson's Spy Company, Texas Cavalry || Capt. Alf Johnson\n|-\n| Denson's Company, Louisiana Cavalry || Capt. William B. Denson\n|-\n| [[10th Texas Light Artillery]] || Capt. Joseph H. Pratt\n|-\n| rowspan=20 | '''Price's Division'''<br>Brig. Gen. [[Daniel M. Frost]]<br>[[File:Brigadier General Daniel Marsh Frost, C.S.A.jpg|thumb|center|upright=0.3|Frost]]\n| rowspan=4 | McRae's Brigade<br>Brig. Gen. [[Dandridge McRae]]\n| [[32nd Arkansas Infantry Regiment]] || Col. L. C. Gause\n|-\n| [[36th Arkansas Infantry Regiment]] || Col. J. E. Glenn\n|-\n| [[39th Arkansas Infantry Regiment]] || Col. R. A. Hart\n|-\n| [[3rd Arkansas Field Battery]] || Capt. John G. Marshall\n|-\n| rowspan=6 | Parsons's Brigade<br>Brig. Gen. [[Mosby Monroe Parsons|M. Monroe Parsons]]\n| [[7th Missouri Infantry Regiment (Confederate)|7th Missouri Infantry Regiment]] || Col. L. M. Lewis\n|-\n| [[8th Missouri Infantry Regiment (Confederate)|8th Missouri Infantry Regiment]] || Col. S. P. Burns\n|-\n| [[9th Missouri Infantry Regiment (Confederate)|9th Missouri Infantry Regiment]] || Col. J. D. White\n|-\n| [[10th Missouri Infantry Regiment (Confederate)|10th Missouri Infantry Regiment]] || Col. A. C. Pickett\n|-\n| [[9th Missouri Sharpshooter Battalion (Confederate)|9th Missouri Sharpshooter Battalion]] || Maj. L. A. Pindall\n|-\n| [[3rd Missouri Field Battery (Confederate)|3rd Missouri Field Battery]] (4 6lb Gun){{sfn|McGhee|2008|p=13}} || Capt. C. B. Tilden\n|-\n| rowspan=5 | Fagan's Brigade<br>Brig. Gen. [[James Fleming Fagan|James F. Fagan]]\n| [[6th Arkansas Infantry Regiment]] || Col. [[Alexander Travis Hawthorn|Alexander T. Hawthorn]]\n|-\n| [[34th Arkansas Infantry Regiment]] || Col. W. H. Brooks\n|-\n