ports/709089929/ |title=QB Newton faces different challenge in Year 2 |last=Reed |first=Steve |date=September 7, 2012 |website=Daily Herald |language=en-US |access-date=December 24, 2019}}</ref>\n* Most combined yards for a rookie in NFL history (4,784)<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://profootballtalk.nbcsports.com/2015/06/02/panthers-announce-five-year-extension-for-cam-newton/ |title=Panthers announce five-year extension for Cam Newton |last=Alper |first=Josh |date=June 2, 2015 |website=ProFootballTalk |language=en |access-date=December 24, 2019}}</ref>\n* First rookie to pass for at least 4,000 yards<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://pfref.com/tiny/5P4Us |title=Rookies to throw for over 4,000 passing yards in a single season, NFL history |website=Pro-Football-Reference.com |language=en |access-date=December 24, 2019}}</ref>\n* First and only rookie to pass for more than 4,000 yards and rush for more than 700 yards<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://pfref.com/tiny/0i6Zf|title=Rookies to pass for more than 4,000 yards and rush for more than 700 yards in a single season, NFL history |website=Pro-Football-Reference.com |language=en |access-date=December 24, 2019}}</ref>\n* First rookie in NFL history to pass for more than 400 yards in back to back games, September 11, 2011 against the [[Arizona Cardinals]] and September 18, 2011 against the [[Green Bay Packers]]<ref name=\"CamPassRecords\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.cbssports.com/mcc/blogs/entry/22475988/32080252 |title=Cam Newton breaks more rookie passing records |last=Brinson |first=Will |website=CBSSports.com |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130603000836/http://www.cbssports.com/mcc/blogs/entry/22475988/32080252 |archive-date=June 3, 2013 |access-date=December 24, 2019}}</ref> (Record beat by Andrew Luck)\n\n===Records and achievements===\n* Most rushing touchdowns by a quarterback in NFL history (58)<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.si.com/nfl/2016/09/08/carolina-panthers-cam-newton-rushing-touchdowns-record |title=Newton sets record for most rushing TDs by a QB |date=September 8, 2016 |website=SI.com |access-date=November 20, 2019}}</ref>\n* Most passing yards by a quarterback in his first two games (854), September 11, 2011 against the Arizona Cardinals and September 18, 2011 against the [[2011 Green Bay Packers season|Green Bay Packers]]<ref name=\"Panthers30-23\">{{Cite news |url=http://abcnews.go.com/Sports/wireStory/rodgers-packers-beat-newton-panthers-30-23-14549417 |title=Rodgers, Packers Beat Newton, Panthers 30\u201323 |last=Beard |first=Aaron |date=September 18, 2011 |access-date=September 18, 2011 |website=ABCNews.com}}</ref>\n* Most games in NFL history with a passing touchdown and a rushing touchdown (32)<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.si.com/nfl/2016/09/08/carolina-panthers-cam-newton-rushing-touchdowns-record |title=Cam Newton sets NFL record for most rushing touchdowns by a quarterback |date=September 8, 2016 |website=SI.com |access-date=November 20, 2019}}</ref>\n* Most player of the week awards in a single season (5) tied with [[Tom Brady]]<ref name=\"ALCAM\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.al.com/sports/2016/01/cam_newton_adds_another_record.html |title=Cam Newton adds another record in tying Tom Brady's awards mark |last=Inabinett |first=Mark |date=January 6, 2016 |website=AL.com |language=en |access-date=November 20, 2019}}</ref>\n* First player in NFL history and most games with at least 250 passing yards, 100 rushing yards, 1 passing touchdown, and 1 rushing touchdown in a single game (2)<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://pfref.com/tiny/teXjX |title=Players with at least 250 passing yards, 100 rushing yards, 1 passing touchdown, and 1 rushing touchdown in a single game, NFL history |website=Pro-Football-Reference.com |access-date=December 23, 2019}}</ref>\n* Most games in single season with at least one passing touchdown and one rushing touchdown (8)<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.panthers.com/team/roster/cam-newton/a9ff8c76-7a6a-4e1a-9e9a-b72aff45deb4/ |title=Cam Newton Player Biography |website=Panthers.com |access-date=November 20, 2019}}</ref>\n* Only player in NFL history with at least 30 passing touchdowns and 10 rushing touchdowns in same season<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://twitter.com/Gil_Brandt/status/683841519661400065 |title=Gil Brandt on Twitter |website=Twitter |access-date=February 8, 2016}}</ref>\n* Most rushing touchdowns in single season by a quarterback (14), achieved on December 4, 2011 against the [[2011 Tampa Bay Buccaneers season|Tampa Bay Buccaneers]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://pfref.com/tiny/ndwgS |title=Most rushing touchdowns by a quarterback, single season |website=Pro-Football-Reference.com |access-date=November 28, 2015}}</ref>\n* Most combined yards in a player's first five seasons (21,560)<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://blackandbluereview.com/stats-and-superlatives-bucs-at-panthers-week-17/ |title=Stats and Superlatives: Panthers' Historical Regular Season |last=Voth |first=Bill |website=Black and Blue Review |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160129093125/http://blackandbluereview.com/stats-and-superlatives-bucs-at-panthers-week-17/ |archive-date=January 29, 2016 |access-date=February 8, 2016}}</ref>\n* First quarterback and fifth player in NFL history with at least 500 rushing yards, 5 rushing touchdowns, and 4.8 yards a carry in 5 consecutive NFL seasons<ref name=\"nbcsports\">{{Cite web |url=http://profootballtalk.nbcsports.com/2016/01/04/nfl-morning-after-rex-ryans-revenge-headlines-a-wild-week-17/ |title=NFL morning after: Rex Ryan\u2019s revenge headlines a wild Week 17 |last=Smith |first=Michael David |date=January 4, 2016 |website=ProFootballTalk |access-date=February 8, 2016}}</ref>\n* First quarterback in NFL history to win both [[National Football League Rookie of the Year Award|NFL Offensive Rookie of the Year]] and [[National Football League Most Valuable Player Award|NFL MVP]] at some point in his career.\n* Most passing yards by a quarterback in debut game (422), September 11, 2011 against the Arizona Cardinals<ref name=\"al2\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.al.com/sports/index.ssf/2011/09/rookie_cam_newton_makes_it_two.html |title=Rookie Cam Newton becomes first NFL quarterback to throw for more than 400 yards in first two games |last=Goldberg |first=Charles |date=September 18, 2011 |website=AL.com |access-date=November 20, 2019}}</ref>\n* First quarterback in NFL history to pass for more than 400 yards in first two career starts, September 11, 2011 against the Arizona Cardinals and September 18, 2011 against the Green Bay Packers<ref name=\"CamPassRecords\" />\n* Fastest player to throw for 1,000 yards (at Arizona Cardinals, vs. Green Bay Packers, and vs. Jacksonville Jaguars)<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://wonderlictestsample.com/cam-newtons-wonderlic-test-score/ |title=Cam Newton\u2019s Wonderlic Test Score |date=December 10, 2015 |website=Wonderlic Test Sample |access-date=November 20, 2019}}</ref>\n* Sixth quarterback to throw for 400+ yards in back to back games<ref name=\"al2\" />\n* First player in NFL history with at least five rushing touchdowns and five passing touchdowns in his first five games<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://sports.espn.go.com/fantasy/football/ffl/story?page=TMR111013 |title=Fantasy football advice for Week 6: Sleepers and busts, player rankings, good and bad matchups |last=Berry |first=Matthew |date=October 14, 2011 |website=ESPN.com |access-date=October 23, 2011}}</ref>\n* Twenty-fifth NFL player (and first quarterback) to have 20 rushing touchdowns in first two seasons<ref name=\"pfref\">{{Cite web |url=http://pfref.com/tiny/m2QAp |title=Players with at least 20 rushing touchdowns in their first two seasons, NFL history |website=Pro-Football-Reference.com |access-date=December 23, 2019}}</ref>\n* First player to have 30 passing touchdowns and 20 rushing touchdowns in first two seasons<ref name=\"pfref2\">{{Cite web |url=http://pfref.com/tiny/OI0w3 |title=Players to have 30 passing touchdowns and 20 rushing touchdowns in their first two seasons, NFL history |website=Pro-Football-Reference.com |access-date=December 23, 2019}}</ref>\n* First player in NFL history with 50 passing touchdowns and 25 rushing touchdowns in his first three seasons<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://pfref.com/tiny/thcEJ |title=Players with 50 passing touchdowns and 25 rushing touchdowns in their first three seasons, NFL history |website=Pro-Football-Reference.com |language=en |access-date=December 24, 2019}}</ref>\n* First player in NFL history with 4,000+ passing yards and 10+ rushing touchdowns in a season<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://pfref.com/tiny/cQaA8 |title=Players with  4,000+ passing yards and 10+ rushing touchdowns in a single season, NFL history |website=Pro-Football-Reference.com |access-date=December 23, 2019}}</ref>\n* First player in NFL history with 4,000+ passing yards and 500+ rushing yards in a season<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://pfref.com/tiny/GYuME |title=Players with 4,000+ passing yards and 500+ rushing yards in a season, NFL history |website=Pro-Football-Reference.com |access-date=December 23, 2019}}</ref>\n* First quarterback in NFL history with 100+ pass touchdowns and 25+ rush touchdowns in first five seasons<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://pfref.com/tiny/Sx3pT |title=Players with at least 100 passing touchdowns and 25 rushing touchdowns in their first five seasons, NFL history |website=Pro-Football-Reference.com |language=en |access-date=December 24, 2019}}</ref>\n* First quarterback in NFL history with multiple seasons of 20+ passing touchdowns and 10+ rushing touchdowns in a season<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://pfref.com/tiny/n8XH7 |title=Players with multiple seasons of 20+ passing touchdowns and 10+ rushing touchdowns in a season, NFL history |website=Pro-Football-Reference.com |access-date=December 23, 2019}}</ref>\n* First player in NFL history with 10,000 passing yards and 1,000 rushing yards in his first three seasons<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://pfref.com/tiny/rY82Z |title=10,000 passing yards & 1,000 rushing yards in first 3 seasons |publisher=pro-football-reference.com |access-date=December 10, 2015}}</ref>\n* First player in NFL history with 10,000 passing yards and 2,000 rushing yards in his first four seasons<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://pfref.com/tiny/Ivl8J |title=10,000 passing yards & 2,000 rushing yards in first 4 seasons |publisher=pro-football-reference.com |access-date=December 10, 2015}}</ref>\n* First player in NFL history to have at least 3,000 passing yards and 500 rushing yards in five consecutive seasons<ref name=\"blackandbluereview\">{{Cite web |url=http://blackandbluereview.com/stats-and-superlatives-panthers-giants/2/# |title=Stats and Superlatives: Panthers at Giants |website=Black and Blue Review |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160129221056/http://blackandbluereview.com/stats-and-superlatives-panthers-giants/2/ |archive-date=January 29, 2016 |access-date=February 8, 2016}}</ref>\n* First quarterback in NFL history to rush for 100+ yards and pass for 300+ yards with 5 touchdowns in a single game (December 20, 2015).<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://pfref.com/tiny/Xn0Bx |title=Players to rush for at least 100 yards and pass for at least 300 yards with five touchdowns in a single game, NFL history |website=Pro-Football-Reference.com |access-date=December 21, 2015}}</ref>\n* First player in NFL history with 100+ rush yards and 5 pass touchdowns in a single game<ref name=\"blackandbluereview\" />\n* First player with 3,500 passing yards, 20 passing touchdowns and 10 rushing touchdowns in a single season (2011, 2015)<ref name=\"nbcsports\" />\n* First quarterback in NFL history with 10+ rushing touchdowns in multiple NFL seasons (2011, 2015)<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BAGN9wsjBv2/ |title=Instagram |website=Instagram |access-date=February 8, 2016}}</ref>\n* Fifth quarterback in NFL history with 3+ games with 5+ touchdown passes in a season<ref name=\"blackandbluereview\" />\n* Fourth quarterback to win 17+ straight regular season starts in the Super Bowl era<ref name=\"blackandbluereview\" />\n* Most games in NFL history with at least 200 passing yards and 80 rushing yards with multiple touchdown passes and a rushing touchdown (4 games)<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://pfref.com/tiny/CnHVI |title=Players with the most games in NFL history with at least 200 passing yards and 80 rushing yards with multiple touchdown passes and a rushing touchdown  |website=Pro-Football-Reference.com |access-date=September 29, 2015}}</ref>\n* Third quarterback in NFL history with 2+ passing touchdowns and 1+ rushing touchdown<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://blackandbluereview.com/rapid-reactions-panthers-packers/ |title=Rapid Reactions: Panthers Hold Off Packers, Remain Unbeaten |last=Voth |first=Bill |website=Black and Blue Review |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117113654/http://blackandbluereview.com/rapid-reactions-panthers-packers/ |archive-date=November 17, 2015 |access-date=February 8, 2016}}</ref>\n* Second quarterback in NFL history with 3+ passing touchdowns and 1+ rushing touchdown<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://blackandbluereview.com/cam-newton-rising-in-nfl-record-books/ |title=Updating Cam Newton's Rise in NFL Record Books |last=Voth |first=Bill |website=Black and Blue Review |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117075053/http://blackandbluereview.com/cam-newton-rising-in-nfl-record-books/ |archive-date=November 17, 2015 |access-date=February 8, 2016}}</ref>\n* Most touchdown passes from a player from [[Auburn University|Auburn]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.al.com/sports/index.ssf/2015/10/cam_newton_sets_auburn_nfl_rec.html |title=Cam Newton sets Auburn NFL record |last=Inabinett |first=Mark |date=October 4, 2015 |website=AL.com |access-date=February 8, 2016}}</ref>\n* First starting quarterback to win the [[NFC South]] in consecutive seasons (2013\u20132015)\n* Second player in NFL history with 7,500+ pass yards and 40+ pass touchdowns in first two seasons, joining Peyton Manning ('99)<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.scout.com/nfl/panthers/story/1637785-qb-comparison-cam-newton-vs-peyton-manning |title=Comparing Quarterbacks: Cam Newton vs. Peyton Manning |last=Goyette |first=Kenan |website=Scout.com |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160312101943/http://www.scout.com/nfl/panthers/story/1637785-qb-comparison-cam-newton-vs-peyton-manning |archive-date=March 12, 2016}}</ref>\n* First quarterback in NFL history to earn a comeback victory when trailing in overtime<ref name=\"footballoutsiders.com\" />\n* Third quarterback in NFL history to pass for over 3,000 yards in his first five seasons<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://twitter.com/MichaelDavSmith/status/676769741567090688 |title=Cam Newton is the only NFL player with at least five rushing touchdowns in each of the last five seasons. Not the only QB. The only player. |date=December 15, 2015 |website=Twitter |access-date=February 8, 2016}}</ref>\n* Second most 5+ touchdown games in a single season (3)<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.charlotteobserver.com/sports/nfl/carolina-panthers/article50795345.html |title=Carolina Panthers beat Giants 38-35 on Graham Gano\u2019s last-second FG |last=Jones |first=Jonathan |website=The Charlotte Observer |access-date=February 8, 2016}}</ref>\n* Second quarterback with 300+ passing yards and 100+ rushing yards in a single game<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/blogs/nfl-shutdown-corner/nfl-winners-and-losers--what-now--denver-broncos--040421665.html |title=NFL Winners and Losers: What now, Denver Broncos? |last=Schwab |first=Frank |date=December 21, 2015 |website=Yahoo Sports |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151221084841/https://sports.yahoo.com/blogs/nfl-shutdown-corner/nfl-winners-and-losers--what-now--denver-broncos--040421665.html |archive-date=December 21, 2015 |access-date=February 8, 2016}}</ref>\n* First player in Super Bowl era to pass for 300 yards and rush for multiple touchdowns in a playoff game<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://blackandbluereview.com/nfc-championship-stats-and-superlatives/ |title=Stats and Superlatives from the NFC Championship |last=Voth |first=Bill |date=January 25, 2016 |website=Black and Blue Review |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160128014959/http://blackandbluereview.com/nfc-championship-stats-and-superlatives/ |archive-date=January 28, 2016}}</ref>\n* Most rushing touchdowns by a quarterback in his first four seasons (33)<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://blackandbluereview.com/cam-newton-first-four-seasons/ |title=On Cam Newton's Birthday, a Look at His First Four Seasons |last=Voth |first=Bill |date=May 11, 2015 |website=Black and Blue Review |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518082724/http://blackandbluereview.com/cam-newton-first-four-seasons/ |archive-date=May 18, 2015 |access-date=May 11, 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Panthers franchise records===\n''Note: records current as of 2017 off-season''<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://pro-football-reference.com/teams/car/ |title=Carolina Panthers Team Encyclopedia |website=Pro-Football-Reference.com |language=en |access-date=February 11, 2017}}</ref>\n* Pass completions, career (1,710), rookie season (310)\n* Pass attempts, career (2,928), playoff game (41, 2016-02-07 N-DEN)\n* Passing yards, career (25,074), game (432, 2011-09-18 GNB), playoff game (335, 2016-01-24 ARI), rookie season (4,051), rookie game (432, 2011-09-18 GNB)\n* Passing touchdowns, career (158), game (5, thrice, shared with [[Steve Beuerlein]]),<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.charlotteobserver.com/sports/nfl/carolina-panthers/article45921250.html |title=Panthers vs. Washington instant analysis: Cam Newton belongs in MVP race |website=charlotteobserver |access-date=February 8, 2016}}</ref> rookie season (21), rookie game (3, 2011-10-30&nbsp;MIN and 2011-12-24 TAM, shared with [[Kerry Collins]])\n* Interceptions, rookie game (4, 2011-11-20 @DET; shared with [[Kerry Collins]] (twice) and [[Chris Weinke]])\n* Passer Rating, season (99.4 in 2015), game (153.3, 2015-12-13 ATL), playoff career (83.9), rookie season (84.5), rookie game (142.4, 2011-12-24 TAM)\n* Times sacked, career (221), game (9, 2014-11-10 @PHI; shared with [[Frank Reich]]), playoffs (16; shared with [[Jake Delhomme]]), playoff season (8 in 2015; shared with [[Jake Delhomme]]), playoff game (6, 2016-02-07 N-DEN), rookie season (35)\n* Yards per pass attempt, career (7.44), season (7.98 in 2012), game (12.65, 2012-09-16 NOR), playoff season (10.68 in 2013), playoff game (11.96, 2016-01-24 ARI), rookie season (7.84), and rookie game (11.41, 2011-09-11 @ARI)\n* Passing yards per game, career (234.1), playoffs (245.3), playoff season (267 in 2013), and rookie season (253.2)\n* 300+ yard passing games, career (15) and rookie season (3)\n* 4000+ yard passing seasons: 1 (shared with [[Steve Beuerlein]])\n* Rushing touchdowns, career (48), rookie season (14), rookie game (3, 2011-12-04 @TAM; shared with [[Fred Lane (American football)|Fred Lane]])\n* Yards per carry, career (5.18), season (5.83 in 2012), rookie season (5.60)\n* Rush/Rec Touchdowns, playoff game (2; shared with 3 players), rookie season (14), rookie game (3, 2011-12-04 @TAM; shared with [[Fred Lane (American football)|Fred Lane]])\n* Games with 1+ TD, rookie season (10)\n* Games with 2+ TD, rookie season (3)\n* Most combined yards in franchise history<ref name=\"blackandbluereview.com\">{{Cite web |url=http://blackandbluereview.com/redskins-at-panthers-stats-and-superlatives/ |title=A History-Filled Stats and Superlatives |website=Black and Blue Review |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304150529/http://blackandbluereview.com/redskins-at-panthers-stats-and-superlatives/ |archive-date=March 4, 2016 |access-date=February 8, 2016}}</ref>\n* Most NFC Offensive Player of the Week Awards in a single season (5)<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.panthers.com/news/article-2/Newton-not-concerned-with-MVP-chatter/0962c4fd-6b6b-4d50-bf23-3e039291911d |title=Newton not concerned with MVP chatter |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160201212339/http://www.panthers.com/news/article-2/Newton-not-concerned-with-MVP-chatter/0962c4fd-6b6b-4d50-bf23-3e039291911d |archive-date=February 1, 2016 |access-date=February 8, 2016}}</ref>\n* 2nd player in franchise history to win NFC Offensive Player of the Week Award multiple times in a single season<ref name=\"panthers.com\" />\n* Completions in a row (15) (December 6, 2015 vs. [[New Orleans Saints]])<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://twitter.com/ChrisWesseling/status/673660495543459840 |title=Chris Wesseling on Twitter |website=Twitter |access-date=February 8, 2016}}</ref>\n* 1st quarterback in franchise history to throw four TD passes in the first half of a game (November 22, 2015 v [[Washington Redskins]])<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.cbssports.com/nfl/gametracker/recap/NFL_20151122_WAS@CAR/newton-throws-5-tds-unbeaten-panthers-top-redskins-44-16 |title=NFL Recap \u2013 Washington Redskins at Carolina Panthers \u2013 Nov 22, 2015 \u2013 CBSSports.com Game Recap |date=November 22, 2015 |website=CBSSports.com |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151125004201/http://www.cbssports.com/nfl/gametracker/recap/NFL_20151122_WAS%40CAR/newton-throws-5-tds-unbeaten-panthers-top-redskins-44-16 |archive-date=November 25, 2015 |access-date=February 8, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\n[[File:Cam Newton - Carolina Panthers.jpg|thumb|Newton in 2011]]\nNewton is the son of Jackie and Cecil Newton Sr., who was cut as a safety from the pre-season rosters of the [[1983 Dallas Cowboys season|1983 Dallas Cowboys]] and [[1984 Buffalo Bills season|1984 Buffalo Bills]],<ref name=\"Cut-1983\">{{Citation |title=Cowboys Release Eight |date=July 22, 1983 |work=Mid Cities Daily News ([[Mid-Cities]], Texas) |page=8 |publisher=United Press International}}</ref><ref name=\"Cut-1984\">{{Citation |title=Scorebook: Transactions: Football |date=July 24, 1984 |work=The Daily Reporter (Spencer, Iowa) |page=8}}</ref> and the younger brother of [[Cecil Newton|Cecil Newton, Jr.]], a [[Center (American football)|center]] who most recently played for the [[Baltimore Ravens]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.baltimoresun.com/sports/ravens/bal-ravens-add-two-offensive-linemen-to-practice-squad-20111128-story.html |title=Ravens add two offensive linemen to practice squad |last=Lee |first=Edward |date=November 28, 2011 |website=[[The Baltimore Sun]] (blog) |access-date=December 23, 2019}}</ref> His youngest brother, Caylin, is starting quarterback for the [[Howard Bison football|Howard Bison]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sportingnews.com/ncaa-football-news/4654104-cam-newton-brother-caylin-newton-highlight-video-spin-move-grady-hs-recruiting |title=Cam Newton's brother is already a football wunderkind |website=Sporting News |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151104211205/http://www.sportingnews.com/ncaa-football-news/4654104-cam-newton-brother-caylin-newton-highlight-video-spin-move-grady-hs-recruiting |archive-date=November 4, 2015 |access-date=October 29, 2015}}</ref> Newton was also a talented [[baseball]] and [[basketball]] player as a youth but developed a fear of being [[hit by pitch|hit by a pitch]] in baseball and could not avoid [[foul out (basketball)|foul trouble]] on the basketball court. He stopped playing baseball at 14 years old and quit basketball shortly into his high school career.<ref name=\"path2pros\">{{Cite news |url=http://espn.go.com/nfl/story/_/id/9407038/carolina-panthers-cam-newton-path-pros-espn-magazine |title=My path to the pros |last=Thompson |first=Carmen R. |date=June 26, 2013 |work=[[ESPN the Magazine]] |access-date=November 3, 2015 |publisher=[[ESPN]]}}</ref>\n\nNewton is a [[Christians|Christian]]. Newton spoke about his faith after winning the 2011 BCS National Championship Game saying, \"It\u2019s just a God thing. I thank God every single day. I\u2019m just His instrument and He\u2019s using me on a consistent basis daily.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://bcnn1wp.wordpress.com/2012/01/01/cam-newton-its-just-a-god-thing/ |title=Cam Newton: 'It\u2019s Just a God Thing' |last=Whyte |first=Daniel III |date=January 1, 2012 |website=BCNN1WP.wordpress.com |access-date=September 18, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn addition to his commitment to football, Newton participates in motivational speaking.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://camnewtonfoundation.org/cam-newton/ |title=Cam Newton |website=The Cam Newton Foundation |access-date=October 24, 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn December 9, 2014, Newton was involved in a car crash in Charlotte; his vehicle flipped. Newton suffered two back fractures and was held overnight at the hospital for observation. Witnesses claim that the truck Newton was driving rolled over multiple times.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://myfox8.com/2014/12/09/panthers-quarterback-cam-newton-injured-in-uptown-car-wreck/ |title=Cam Newton injured in uptown Charlotte car wreck |date=December 9, 2014 |website=myfox8.com |access-date=December 9, 2014}}</ref> Newton would make a full recovery in 12 days.\n\nNewton graduated from Auburn with a degree in [[sociology]] in the spring of 2015.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.charlotteobserver.com/sports/nfl/carolina-panthers/article20340339.html/ |title=Carolina Panthers QB Cam Newton won\u2019t walk at Auburn graduation |last=Jones |first=Jonathan |website=The Charlotte Observer |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190213224153/https://www.charlotteobserver.com/sports/nfl/carolina-panthers/article20340339.html |archive-date=February 13, 2019 |access-date=June 3, 2015}}</ref>\n\nNewton was formerly a self-proclaimed [[Pescetarianism|pescetarian]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/blog/carolina-panthers/post/_/id/2449 |title=Newton scales back for Thanksgiving meal |last=Newton |first=David |date=November 26, 2013 |website=ESPN.com |language=en |access-date=August 2, 2019}}</ref> As of March 2019 he has become a [[veganism|vegan]],<ref>{{Cite AV media |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8-UT6Hi-lHM |title=getting my body ready for next season |date=March 15, 2019 |last=Newton |first=Cam |publisher=YouTube |work=Cam Newton Vlogs}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://pantherswire.usatoday.com/2019/03/15/panthers-cam-newton-youtube-channel-vegan/ |title=Watch: Cam Newton says he's gone vegan in new Youtube video |last=Weaver |first=Tim |date=March 15, 2019 |website=Panthers Wire |publisher=USA Today Sports |language=en |access-date=May 27, 2019}}</ref> though some dietitians have linked this change in diet to his delayed injury recovery the following season.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.charlotteobserver.com/sports/nfl/carolina-panthers/article235295427.html |title=How Cam Newton\u2019s vegan diet may be hurting Panthers QB\u2019s play and injury recovery |last=Marks |first=Brendan |date=September 27, 2019 |work=The Charlotte Observer |accessdate=December 18, 2019}}</ref>\n\nNewton partnered with Southern department store chain [[Belk]] on his own clothing line, MADE by Cam Newton.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.esquire.com/style/mens-fashion/interviews/a21683/cam-newton-interview-0413/ |title=The ESQ&A: Cam Newton on His New Clothing Line |last=Screws |first=Nic |date=April 9, 2013 |website=Esquire |access-date=February 8, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn December 30, 2015, Newton confirmed on [[Twitter]] that his girlfriend, Kia Proctor, gave birth to a son on December 24, 2015, in Atlanta.<ref name=\"Newton announces birth of son\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.charlotteobserver.com/sports/nfl/carolina-panthers/article52361270.html |title=Panthers QB Cam Newton announces birth of son |last=Jones |first=Jonathan |date=December 30, 2015 |website=Charlotte Observer |publisher=The Charlotte Observer |access-date=October 1, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Chosen\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.charlotteobserver.com/sports/nfl/carolina-panthers/article52527660.html |title=Panthers QB Cam Newton has 'glow' after welcoming a son named Chosen |last=Jones |first=Jonathan |date=December 31, 2015 |website=Charlotte Observer |publisher=The Charlotte Observer |access-date=January 1, 2016}}</ref> In February 2017, Newton and Proctor's daughter was born.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://blackandbluereview.com/cam-newton-baby-daughter-born/ |title=Cam Newton\u2019s Baby Daughter Has Arrived |last=Voth |first=Bill |website=Black And Blue Review |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170315174258/http://blackandbluereview.com/cam-newton-baby-daughter-born/ |archive-date=March 15, 2017 |access-date=March 14, 2017}}</ref> Proctor gave birth to the couple's third child, a boy, in July 2018.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thescore.com/nfl/news/1568483 |title=Cam Newton, girlfriend Kia Proctor welcome 3rd child |last=Holroyd |first=Caitlyn |date=July 8, 2018 |website=theScore.com |access-date=August 2, 2019}}</ref> Their fourth child was born in October 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.wnct.com/sports/carolina-panthers/girlfriend-of-carolina-panthers-quarterback-cam-newton-shares-photo-of-newborn-baby/ |title=Girlfriend of Carolina Panthers quarterback Cam Newton shares photo of newborn baby |last=WGHP |date=October 17, 2019 |access-date=October 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn January 29, 2019, Newton announced plans for his first business venture, Fellaship, a cigar bar-restaurant located near Mercedes-Benz Stadium in downtown Atlanta.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.bizjournals.com/atlanta/news/2019/01/29/cam-newton-set-to-open-cigar-bar-lounge-near.html |title=Cam Newton set to open cigar bar-lounge near Mercedes-Benz Stadium |last=Mandel |first=Eric |date=January 20, 2019 |website=Atlanta Business Chronicle |access-date=January 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[2010 College Football All-America Team]]\n* [[List of first overall National Football League draft picks]]\n* [[List of Heisman Trophy winners]]\n* [[List of National Football League career passer rating leaders]]\n* [[List of National Football League career passing completions leaders]] \n* [[List of National Football League career passing touchdowns leaders]] \n* [[List of National Football League career quarterback wins leaders]]\n* [[List of National Football League records (individual)]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* Layden, Tim. \"The Real Thing\". ''Sports Illustrated Kids'' 23.10 (2011): 50. Article on Cam Newton's first three games in the NFL.\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110804045749/http://www.panthers.com/team/roster/Cam-Newton/a9ff8c76-7a6a-4e1a-9e9a-b72aff45deb4 Carolina Panthers bio]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20100914131249/http://auburntigers.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/mtt/newton_cameron00.html Auburn Tigers bio]\n* {{Heisman|id=76|name=Cam Newton}}\n* {{Footballstats |nfl=2495455 |espn=13994 |pfr=NewtCa00}}\n* 2009 college stats from [https://web.archive.org/web/20160203174900/http://www.njcaa.org/sports/fball/2009-10/teams/BlinnCollege/players/CameronNewton.html NJCAA.org]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCyKV3Zl7AKVj7ikyOlcfZTQ Official YouTube channel]\n\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Cam Newton\u2014awards, championships, and honors\n| list1 =\n{{2008 Florida Gators football navbox}}\n{{Auburn Tigers quarterback navbox}}\n{{2010 Auburn Tigers football navbox}}\n{{Heisman Trophy}}\n{{Maxwell Award}}\n{{Manning Award}}\n{{Walter Camp Award}}\n{{Davey O'Brien Award}}\n{{Southeastern Conference Football Player of the Year navbox}}\n{{AP Players of the Year}}\n{{Sporting News College Football Player of the Year}}\n{{2010 NCAA Division I FBS College Football Consensus All-Americans}}\n{{NFL Number One Draft Picks}}\n{{2011 NFL Draft}}\n{{PanthersFirstPick}}\n{{Panthers2011DraftPicks}}\n{{Carolina Panthers starting quarterback navbox}}\n{{Diet Pepsi NFL Rookie of the Year}}\n{{AP Offensive Rookies of the Year}}\n{{AP Offensive Players of 